class Solution {
    public int trap(int[] height) {
        int l = 0, r = height.length - 1, lmax = 0, rmax = 0, result = 0;
        while (l < r) {
            if (height[l] < height[r]) {
                lmax = Math.max(lmax, height[l]);
                result += lmax - height[l];
                l++;
            } else {
                rmax = Math.max(rmax, height[r]);
                result += rmax - height[r];
                r--;
            }
        }
        return result;
    }
}





# 42. Trapping Rain Water

## 🧩 Pattern
Two Pointers

## 💡 Key Trick
Track lmax and rmax. Water trapped at any index depends on the smaller of the two max heights. Move the pointer with the smaller height.

## ⏱️ Complexity
Time: O(n)
Space: O(1)

## 🧠 Alternative Approaches
- Brute force: O(n²) (for each index, find left max & right max)
- Prefix + Suffix arrays: O(n) time, O(n) space